"Zsabokorszky F.","Socio-political reception of sewage sludge recycling: The Hungarian perspective",2011,"Journal of Residuals Science and Technology","8","4",,"159","164",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-82255180482&partnerID=40&md5=07d17c2c7593699b9c2bf2c74d8ea530","ENQUA Kft, Hungary","Zsabokorszky, F., ENQUA Kft, Hungary","The management of sewage sludge is facing new challenges in the early 21st century. It accounts for an ever-larger proportion of the costs of wastewater treatment. In Hungary, water utilities and land suitable for agricultural recycling have a new structure of ownership as a result of post-transition privatisation, with fundamental consequences for sludge use. A new factor, climate change, may make wastewater irrigation-particularly for energy crops-an important feature of water management in areas global warming have rendered arid. As the increasing costs of sludge treatment are passed on to the customers, service charges are expected to rise, having a potentially adverse effect on water use. © 2011 DEStech Publications, Inc.",,"Adverse effect; Hungarians; Hungary; Sludge treatment; Water use; Water utility; Crops; Electric utilities; Global warming; Privatization; Sewage sludge; Wastewater; Wastewater reclamation; Wastewater treatment; Water management; Water supply; Water recycling; energy crop; global warming; irrigation system; ownership; privatization; recycling; sewage treatment; sludge; twenty first century; water industry; water use; Hungary",,,,,,"Papp Dr., M., A Vízigény várható alakulásának vizsgálata (2007), MAVÍZwww.epito.bme.hu, Vízellátás és települések csatornázása-Jelenlegi problémák és jövó́béli feladatok(1991), The Council Directive 91/271/EEC concerning urban waste-water treatment was adopted on 21 MayJuhász, E.D., Iszapkezelés és hasznosítás helyzete és lehetó́ségei (2010) Hírcsatorna, 4, p. 11; ødegaard, H., Paulsrud, B., Karlsson, I., Sludge disposal strategies and corresponding treatment technolog